President Obama met with Prime Minister Saad Hariri of Lebanon and commended him for his leadership and carrying on his father's legacy. They discussed Lebanon's term as President of the U.N. Security Council and their commitment to strengthening Lebanon's sovereignty and independence. They also reviewed progress on bilateral and regional issues, such as Arab-Israeli peace and UN Security Council Resolutions. The President emphasized the importance of Iran's compliance with nonproliferation obligations and the threat posed by weapons transfer into Lebanon. President Obama expressed his determination to support and strengthen Lebanese institutions, contribute to economic growth, and reaffirmed the United States' support for the Special Tribunal for Lebanon.